<emphasis italics="true" pageId="493" pageNumber="494">q.v</emphasis>
.] and the Latin suffix - 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="493" pageNumber="494">ius</emphasis>
(pertaining to), alluding to the close affinity of the taxon to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1831" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Abaris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="493" pageNumber="494" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="493" pageNumber="494">Abaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(&quot; 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="493" pageNumber="494">
pour indiquer son 
<normalizedToken originalValue="affinitÃ©">affinite</normalizedToken>
avec les vrais Abarys
</emphasis>
&quot;) [masculine].
</paragraph>
